According to realtor website [[Zillow]], the average price of a home as of October 31, 2025, in Thompson is $356,166.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Thompson, ND Housing Market |url=https://www.zillow.com/home-values/56729/thompson-nd/ |publisher=[[Zillow]] |access-date=December 10, 2025 |language=en}}</ref>

As of the 2023 [[American Community Survey]], there are 412 estimated households in Thompson with an average of 2.65 persons per household. The city has a median household income of $110,909. Approximately 1.0% of the city's population lives at or below the [[Poverty in the United States|poverty line]]. Thompson has an estimated 75.3% employment rate, with 39.7% of the population holding a bachelor's degree or higher and 98.1% holding a high school diploma.<ref name="QF">{{Cite web|title=U.S. Census Bureau QuickFacts: Thompson city, North Dakota |url=https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/fact/table/thompsoncitynorthdakota/PST045224 |access-date=December 10, 2025 |website=www.census.gov |language=en}}</ref> There were 439 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1016.20|/sqmi|/km2|1}}.

The top five reported languages (people were allowed to report up to two languages, thus the figures will generally add to more than 100%) were English (99.1%), Spanish (0.7%), Indo-European (0.0%), Asian and Pacific Islander (0.2%), and Other (0.0%).

The median age in the city was 44.5 years.

