===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], there were 1,101 people, 387 households, and 319 families residing in the city.<ref>{{Cite web|title=U.S. Census Bureau, Table P16: Household Type |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Thompson%20city,%20North%20Dakota%20p16&y=2020 |access-date=December 10, 2025 |publisher=United States Census Bureau}}</ref> The [[population density]] was {{convert|2352.56|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 396 housing units at an average density of {{convert|846.15|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the city was 92.55% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.09% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.64% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.09% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.09% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 1.00% from some other races and 5.54% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] people of any race were 3.45% of the population.<ref>{{Cite web|title=How many people live in Thompson city, North Dakota |url=https://data.usatoday.com/census/total-population/total-population-change/thompson-city-north-dakota/160-3878660/ |publisher=[[USA Today]] |access-date=December 10, 2025}}</ref>

===2010 census===
As of the [[2010 United States census|2010 census]], there were 986 people, 356 households, and 293 families living in the city. The population density was {{convert|2143.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 362 housing units at an average density of {{convert|787.0|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the city was 98.07% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.30% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 1.01% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.10% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.00% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.10% from some other races and 0.41% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] people of any race were 0.91% of the population.

There were 356 households, of which 42.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 73.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 7.0% had a female householder with no husband present, 2.2% had a male householder with no wife present, and 17.7% were non-families. 14.9% of all households were made up of individuals, and 4.8% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.77 and the average family size was 3.04.

The median age in the city was 36.8 years. 28.4% of residents were under the age of 18; 6.9% were between the ages of 18 and 24; 27.2% were from 25 to 44; 30.5% were from 45 to 64; and 7.1% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the city was 51.0% male and 49.0% female.

===2000 census===
As of the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], there were 1,006 people, 329 households, and 273 families living in the city. The population density was {{convert|2177.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 339 housing units at an average density of {{convert|733.8|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the city was 97.71% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.40% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.10% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.70% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.20% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.89% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] people of any race were 0.80% of the population.

There were 329 households, out of which 53.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 74.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 4.3% had a female householder with no husband present, and 17.0% were non-families. 15.2% of all households were made up of individuals, and 6.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 3.06 and the average family size was 3.43.

In the city, the population was spread out, with 34.9% under the age of 18, 6.3% from 18 to 24, 33.4% from 25 to 44, 19.8% from 45 to 64, and 5.7% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 33 years. For every 100 females, there were 105.7 males. For every 100 females aged 18 and over, there were 97.9 males.

The median income for a household in the city was $54,514, and the median income for a family was $57,250. Males had a median income of $35,682 versus $21,298 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $19,857. None of the families and 0.7% of the population were living below the [[Poverty threshold|poverty line]], including no under eighteens and 7.7% of those over 64.

